# Proof-system discipline

This rule auto-attaches whenever the agent reads or edits a file under
`src/proof.rs`, `src/vanillastark/**`, `src/stwo_backend/**`, or `tests/**`.

## Hard invariants

- The `statement-v1` semantic scope literally names a transformer/native
  equivalence check. Every public verification entry point in `src/proof.rs`
  must reject any v1-scoped claim that drops `claim.equivalence` or
  `claim.transformer_config`. Do not relax `validate_equivalence_metadata`
  or `validate_transformer_config` for the v1 scope.
- `cargo clippy --lib --no-deps -- -D warnings` is currently green for the
  lib target. New code must keep it green.
- Frozen artifact bundles under `docs/paper/artifacts/` cite specific byte
  hashes. Do not change FRI sampler behavior, omicron-domain construction,
  Merkle leaf encoding, or any other proof-byte-affecting code on the
  vanilla-v1 backend without an explicit `proof_backend_version` bump and
  a coordinated bundle regeneration. The `Fri::sample_index_full_entropy`
  helper is staged but intentionally unwired for this reason.
- The `production-v1` STARK profile is a CI smoke profile, not a
  cryptographic claim (32 conjectured bits, 16 conservative). For any
  publication-cited proof use `publication-v1` (96 conjectured, 48
  conservative). See
  `docs/engineering/release-gates/publication-profile.md`.

## Required test coverage

When the touched code path includes any of:

- a verifier invariant in `src/proof.rs` or `src/vanillastark/stark.rs`,
- the FRI commit / verify / sample paths,
- a Merkle commit / open / verify path,
- the Stwo carried-state, manifest, or backend-version surface,
- any `*_VERSION_*`, `*_SCOPE_*`, or claim-commitment constant,

the change MUST add or update at least one of:

- a negative test that constructs a malformed input and asserts the new
  invariant rejects it,
- a tamper-path test that mutates a known-good artifact byte and asserts
  rejection,
- a regression test that pins the new behavior under all public entry
  points (loop over `verify_execution_stark`, `_claim_only`, `_with_policy`,
  `_with_reexecution`, etc.).

After adding the test, run `just proof-tests` (for proof.rs / vanillastark
edits) or `just lib` (for stwo_backend edits), then `just gate` before
reporting work as done.

## Spec-sync

`spec/statement-v1.json` and the `CLAIM_*_V1` constants in `src/proof.rs`
are pinned together by the
`statement_spec_contract_is_synced_with_constants` test. If you change one,
change the other in the same edit.

## Naming honesty

Do not introduce or rename a `.tvm` fixture under `programs/` whose name
implies a model family the program does not faithfully implement. The
existing `programs/gemma_block_*.tvm` fixtures are tracked for rename in
`docs/engineering/release-gates/naming-honesty.md`. If you touch them,
follow the rename plan there.
